[2] Nigeria - Bauchi, positive environmental samples cVDPV2
Date: Fri 19 Oct 2018
Source: NTA [edited]
http://www.nta.ng/news/domestic/20181019-type-2-polio-virus-found-in-bauchi-who/


Type 2 polio virus found in Bauchi - WHO
-------------------
The World Health Organisation (WHO) says circulating vaccine-derived polio virus type 2 (cVDPV2) has been discovered in Bauchi State. Dr. Adamu Ningi, the WHO Bauchi state coordinator, disclosed this at a meeting with the emir of Bauchi, Alhaji Rilwanu Adamu, and the chairman, social mobilisation on immunisation and emir of Dass, Alhaji Usman Othman, in Bauchi on Friday [19 Oct 2018].

Ningi said samples were collected from various locations on a monthly basis, and it has been discovered that the polio virus type 2 was found at the Gwallaga mosque area linking 3 wards of Makama B, Hardo, and Dankade.

Represented by Dr. Khalid Abubakar, the state coordinator attributed the new strain to non-compliance to immunisation schedules. "In Bauchi LGA [local government authority], only 52 percent of children are fully immunised, 29 percent didn't complete, and 19 percent have never been immunised."

"The latest strain of the virus are from isolated environmental samples collected from Gwallaga mosque area, Obonna Royal Hotel refuse site, Shafa bridge, and FGGC [Federal Government Girls College] drainage," he added. The circulating vaccine-derived polio virus is linked to the one earlier discovered in Hadejia, Jigawa State."

Also speaking, the state chairman, social mobilisation on immunisation, said the state has been without any reported case of polio for over 5 years. Othman said he regretted to have to record a new case despite efforts to prevent [the disease's] resurgence from reported cases in Yobe and Jigawa states.

He noted that immunisation teams failed to report non-compliance cases in the past while supervision was poor. The 1st-class traditional ruler said the meeting was designed to engage the traditional institution and seek ways to contain the virus. According to Othman, since the detection, WHO, UNICEF, the state government, and traditional leaders have intensified efforts to check its spread.

In his remarks, the emir of Bauchi emphasised the need for ward heads to always accompany house-to-house teams during immunisation, plus days to avoid non-compliance. Although promising to support to eradicate the virus in his domain, Adamu, charged governments and the general public to intensify environmental sanitation and close supervision.

Speaking earlier, Dr. Shakhawar Hossain, the UNICEF state lead communication officer, said intense campaigns must be mounted, and traditional leaders should be on ground to answer key questions on polio immunisation.

[Byline: Inno.Korie]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The above represents evidence that the cVDPV2 virus from Jigawa state is circulating significantly in Bauchi LGA, as seen through the identification of the virus in environmental samples taken from 4 different sites. The information that only 52 percent of children are fully immunized, 29 percent are partially immunized, and 19 percent have never been immunized in Jigawa is the perfect background "storm waiting to happen" for circulation of a cVDPV or WPV in the area. It appears as though the storm is starting. It should be noted that falling vaccination coverages are not uncommon when the disease hasn't been seen in an area for a while.

A map of Nigeria showing states can be found at: http://www.waado.org/nigerdelta/Maps/Nigeria_States.html. Bauchi is in the north-central part of Nigeria, with a sizable border to its north with Jigawa and its northeast with Yobe, both states with extensive transmission of cVDPV2. - Mod.MPP

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map:
Bauchi State, Nigeria: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6102512,3741]
